\section{Discussion}

The results demonstrate that trustworthiness depends on reasoning transparency and safety monitoring rather than predictive accuracy alone.

Systems with active safety supervision produced higher trust indices even when raw accuracy remained unchanged.

\section{Conclusion}

Trust-X demonstrates that trustworthy clinical AI requires transparency, consensus reasoning, and operational safety.

Future work will explore larger clinical datasets and improved reasoning evaluation methods.

